#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:91
msgid "The user interface is summarized in vtkInteractorStyle.h:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:93
msgid ""
"Keypress j / Keypress t: toggle between joystick (position sensitive) and "
"trackball (motion sensitive) styles. In joystick style, motion occurs "
"continuously as long as a mouse button is pressed. In trackball style, "
"motion occurs when the mouse button is pressed and the mouse pointer moves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:99
msgid ""
"Keypress c / Keypress o: toggle between camera and object (actor) modes. In "
"camera mode, mouse events affect the camera position and focal point. In "
"object mode, mouse events affect the actor that is under the mouse pointer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:104
msgid ""
"Button 1: rotate the camera around its focal point (if camera mode) or "
"rotate the actor around its origin (if actor mode). The rotation is in the "
"direction defined from the center of the renderer's viewport towards the "
"mouse position. In joystick mode, the magnitude of the rotation is "
"determined by the distance the mouse is from the center of the render window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:111
msgid ""
"Button 2: pan the camera (if camera mode) or translate the actor (if object "
"mode). In joystick mode, the direction of pan or translation is from the "
"center of the viewport towards the mouse position. In trackball mode, the "
"direction of motion is the direction the mouse moves. (Note: with 2-button "
"mice, pan is defined as <Shift>-Button 1.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:111
msgid "<Shift>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:118
msgid ""
"Button 3: zoom the camera (if camera mode) or scale the actor (if object "
"mode). Zoom in/increase scale if the mouse position is in the top half of "
"the viewport; zoom out/decrease scale if the mouse position is in the bottom "
"half. In joystick mode, the amount of zoom is controlled by the distance of "
"the mouse pointer from the horizontal centerline of the window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:125
msgid ""
"Keypress 3: toggle the render window into and out of stereo mode.  By "
"default, red-blue stereo pairs are created. Some systems support Crystal "
"Eyes LCD stereo glasses; you have to invoke SetStereoTypeToCrystalEyes() on "
"the rendering window.  Note: to use stereo you also need to pass a stereo=1 "
"keyword argument to the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:132
msgid "Keypress e: exit the application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:134
msgid "Keypress f: fly to the picked point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:136
msgid ""
"Keypress p: perform a pick operation. The render window interactor has an "
"internal instance of vtkCellPicker that it uses to pick."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:139
msgid ""
"Keypress r: reset the camera view along the current view direction. Centers "
"the actors and moves the camera so that all actors are visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:143
msgid ""
"Keypress s: modify the representation of all actors so that they are "
"surfaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:146
msgid ""
"Keypress u: invoke the user-defined function. Typically, this keypress will "
"bring up an interactor that you can type commands in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/qt/QVTKRenderWindowInteractor.py:149
msgid ""
"Keypress w: modify the representation of all actors so that they are "
"wireframe."
msgstr ""

